Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Peel and finely chop the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and finely chopped) and roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1}(roughly chopped). Peel and chop the @carrot{2}(peeled and chopped into sticks). Chop any large @new potatoes{2}(chopped into quarters) into quarters.

Pat the @chicken thighs{8} skin dry with some #kitchen paper{}. Rub a ¼ tsp of @olive oil{1/4%tsp} on each thigh and rub in a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Place on a #baking tray{} and cook in your #oven{} on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes}, until the skin is nice and crispy. Rest them out of the oven afterwards.

Bring a large #pot{} of water with a pinch of salt to the boil and add in your potatoes. After ~{12%minutes}, add your carrot to the pot and cook everything together for another ~{4%minutes}.

> Cooking your carrots with the potatoes saves on dirty pots and boiling more water.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @olive oil{splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once it's hot, add in the @chorizo{2}(diced). When the chorizo has browned off slightly add in your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

> Be careful not to burn the garlic.

Add in the @chopped tomatoes{2}(canned), mushrooms and @bay leaf{2}. Refill the tin with 2cm of water, swirl around and add to the pan too. Next stir in a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Leave to bubble away on low heat until it has thickened up (about ~{15%minutes}).

The potatoes should be soft enough to slip a sharp #knife{} through them by now. Drain the water and put your carrots in a separate #bowl{}. Let your potatoes dry off and crush them lightly with a #fork{}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}.

Heat another frying pan with a splash of @olive oil{splash} on high heat and add the leaves from your @rosemary{1}(fresh, leaves picked). Cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the potatoes and cook until they are crisped up (about ~{5%minutes}).

> You can reheat your carrots with the potatoes for the last minute.

Serve your carrot and crushed potatoes in a bowl and top with your chicken thigh. Pour your chorizo infused tomato sauce over the top. In your most dramatic matador's voice shout 'Olé!' as you serve it on the table.